<subSubSection id="78879BECFFBCFF876DB0834DFEF00AB5" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3022C867FFBCFF876DB0834DFEF00AB5" blockId="1.[151,1436,1814,1984]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis id="02E91475FFBCFF876DB0834DFED80A0D" bold="true" box="[199,322,1886,1912]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male imago: (1) penis lobes widely separated from each other (
<figureCitation id="A8A6D4E2FFBCFF87696B834DFB170A0D" box="[1052,1165,1886,1912]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,879,903]" captionTargetBox="[158,1436,185,855]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,181,855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male subimago of Bessierus doloris. a. forewing; b. body, dorsal view; c. genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4397234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4397234/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Figure 2c</figureCitation>
); (2) base of each penis lobe, on outer margin, without expansion; (3) telopenis broad; (4) inner margin of basal 1/3 of forceps segment I smoothly rounded.
</paragraph>
